title: Delhi: Foetus found in washroom of government hospital, case registered | delhi | Hindustan Times
text:
Delhi: Foetus found in washroom of government hospital, case registered delhi Updated: Feb 21, 2017 09:03 IST PTI New Delhi A case has been registered and efforts are on to identify the person who left the foetus near the toilet seat.(PTI/Representative Photo) 
A five to six month old foetus was found in the washroom of a government hospital in south Delhiâ€™s Malviya Nagar area, police said on Tuesday. 
An attendant found the foetus in the washroom on Monday night and alerted hospital authorities, who in turn informed the police. 
A case has been registered and efforts are on to identify the person who left the foetus near the toilet seat, police said. 
CCTV footage is being analysed and hospital staff is being questioned in the matter, they said. tags
